<subSubSection id="91EB650BFF9DFFA3FD39B5A9FB2DF9F3" pageId="20" pageNumber="171" type="description">
<paragraph id="D94E3680FF9DFFA3FD39B5A9FB2DF9F3" blockId="20.[675,1212,1416,1699]" pageId="20" pageNumber="171">
<emphasis id="EB85EA92FF9DFFA3FD39B5A9FB2DF9F3" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="171">Rhizome suberect to short creeping; rhizome scales light brown. Adult and young fronds always simple, dimorphic: the stipe of fertile ones longer than sterile ones, fertile lamina shorter and much contracted. Sterile lamina linear to narrowly elliptic, 5.0-25.6 × 0.8-1.7 cm, apex more often caudate, base decurrent on the stipe. Sori unbroken; indusium entire.</emphasis>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
